===Etymology===
From {{etyl|de}} {{term|Hamster|lang=de}}, from {{etyl|goh}} ''hamustra'' 'field-mouse', from Russian-{{etyl|cu}} {{term|хомѣсторъ|tr=chomĕstorŭ|lang=cu}}, a [[tautological]] hybrid of {{proto|Slavic|lang=en}} roots *''xoměkъ'' (compare Russian {{term|хомяк|tr=xomják||hamster|lang=ru}}) and *''storъ'' (compare [[Lithuanian]] {{term|staras|stãras|hamster|lang=lt}}).
Alternative Etymology traces {{etyl|goh}} {{term|hamestro|hamustra, hamustro|lang=goh}} to {{proto|Germanic|xamustrō(n-)||xamustran-|hamster|lang=en}} from {{proto|Indo-European|kam-|a kind of rodent|lang=en}}, making it cognate to the {{etyl|cu|-}} word, and to {{etyl|lt|-}} {{term|kãmas||rodent, rat|lang=lt}}. Akin to {{etyl|osx|-}} {{term|hamustra||hamster|lang=osx}}.

